Feedback: It was critical to have Jake Livingstone with the training class. As an instructor Jason excels in conveying the material in a clear and understandable way, but the lack of fundamental understanding is clear when a question comes up related to the material but is not covered in the slides.

Feedback: Jason did well, it was clear that it was his first class so I'd give him some grace. Having a more natural flow would help, at times it was obvious he was just regurgitating the slides and had little real world telecom experience. Over all he did a good job though. In regards to content, I think it'd be much more useful if there was more interactive labs, getting in and solving problems, at least for me, is the best way to learn this content. The class, instructor, and other students all made this week a pleasure and I would definitely recommend it to a colleague.

Lab_Comments: Hope less lab because we can do them in job if needed.
Feedback: No matter how long the training is, I don't think you can cover everything. Something like putty, some provision procedures we can learn at job if needed. I would say, focus on concept is more important. Some procedures if we don't use them, then w never going to touch them.

Appropriate_Time_Comments: Should have attended it when I first deployed perimeta
Recommend_Comments: Its good for people beginning on Perimeta
Feedback: Jason did a good job for his first Perimeta course. Some terms were confused but nothing major, he'll definitely be more comfortable and confident with the details as he does more courses. As far as the course content, theres alot of repetitive slides and very basic it/telecom. Some of the basic content might be too basic, we spent alot of time going over basic SIP signaling and tools rather than actual operations and configurations of the Perimeta itself. Overall I'd love to see more indepth or realworld training/workshops/exersizes for advanced training topics.
